  the fain/kahal catalogue also includes " let a smile be your umbrella " ( 1928 ) with francis wheeler ,   " wedding bells are breaking up that old gang of mine " ( 1929 ) with willie raskin , " by a waterfall " ( 1930 ) , " when i take my sugar to tea " ( 1931 ) with pierre norman , " the night is young and you 're so beautiful " ( 1936 ) , " i can dream , ca n't i ? " ( 1938 ) and " i 'll be seeing you " , which was written in 1938 , but became a hit in 1943 especially among the families of servicemen sent overseas .

